---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="How to Finesse Cheap Flights Across the USA, CAN & MEX" description="Host cities are spread out af. Here is the ultimate hack sheet so you do not go broke.">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-20 px-4 bg-[#F7803C]">
    <article class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl bg-white border-[4px] border-black p-8 md:p-12 shadow-[12px_12px_0px_#2E0D23] relative z-20">
      <div class="inline-block bg-yellow-300 text-black border-[3px] border-black font-black px-4 py-1 uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">TRAVEL & FINANCE</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-6 leading-none" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">
        How to Finesse Cheap Flights Across the USA, CAN & MEX
      </h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-black font-medium leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-black border-l-8 border-l-blue-600">
          Let's state facts: the 2026 World Cup is spread across a massive continent. If you try booking direct flights between Vancouver and Mexico City during the tournament, the airlines will absolutely rob you blind. Here's how to actually survive.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">1. The Border-Hopping Hack (CBX)</h2>
        <p>
          Going to matches in Mexico and California? Do not fly direct from LAX to Mexico City. Instead, fly into San Diego (SAN), use the Cross Border Xpress (CBX) bridge to walk directly into the Tijuana airport (TIJ), and take a domestic Mexican flight on Volaris or VivaAerobus. You will literally save hundreds of dollars avoiding international taxes.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">2. Stop Sleeping on Amtrak (Northeast Corridor)</h2>
        <p>
          If you have tickets for Boston, New York, and Philadelphia, flying is a massive L. The TSA lines alone will make you question your life choices. Book Amtrak's Northeast Regional (or Acela if you're feeling bougie) well in advance. You go city-center to city-center in a few hours without the airport headache.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">3. Secondary Airports Are Your Best Friend</h2>
        <p>
          Skip the major hubs if prices spike. Going to Miami? Fly into Fort Lauderdale (FLL) and take the Brightline train. Going to Dallas? Look at Dallas Love Field (DAL) instead of DFW. Going to LA? Burbank (BUR) or John Wayne (SNA) are infinitely better experiences than LAX.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-blue-100 border-[3px] border-black shadow-[4px_4px_0px_#2E0D23]">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black uppercase mb-2">TL;DR:</h3>
          <p class="font-bold">Never book direct international cross-continent flights during Matchdays. Leverage domestic budgets airlines, trains for the East Coast, and the CBX bridge for Mexico. Gatekeep this info from the casuals.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-between items-center border-t-[4px] border-black pt-6">
        <a href="/blog" class="font-outfit text-xl uppercase text-black hover:text-blue-600 transition-colors">← Back to Guides</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
